      "message": "The problem with these is that we’ve mixed fundamental types (int) with typedefs (int64_t). If it weren’t for that, this wouldn’t need to be protected by OS.\n\nWhat we should do here is just define these in terms of fundamental types, so provide overloads for:\n\nint\nunsigned int\nlong\nunsigned long\nlong long\nunsigned long long\n\n(P.S. if this did need to be protected, we wouldn’t use the compiler predefined macro directly, we’d use something from build/build_config.h: OS_WIN.)",
